<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2018/04/12/spring-security-oauth-2-3-2-released">Spring Security OAuth 2.3.2 Released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/9871b03a6881b8046b250d801197e40a?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/pivotal-joe-grandja">Joe Grandja</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2018-04-12 17:52:11.55">April 12, 2018</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3248" href="/blog/2018/04/12/spring-security-oauth-2-3-2-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><div class="paragraph">
<p>On behalf of the community, I’m pleased to announce the release of Spring Security OAuth 2.3.2.RELEASE.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This release resolves a runtime incompatibility issue with <code>RedisTokenStore</code> and <a href="https://projects.spring.io/spring-data-redis/">Spring Data Redis 2.0.x</a>. See <a href="https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security-oauth/pull/1319">#1319</a> and <a href="https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security-oauth/issues/1335">#1335</a>. This release also includes a few minor enhancements and bug fixes.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><a href="https://projects.spring.io/spring-security-oauth/">Project Page</a> | <a href="https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security-oauth/">GitHub</a> | <a href="https://projects.spring.io/spring-security-oauth/docs/Home.html">Documentation</a> | <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/spring-security-oauth2">Help</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2018/04/12/spring-security-oauth-2-3-2-released">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
